Etymology[edit]

From prae- +‎ sāgiō.

Verb[edit]

praesāgiō (present infinitive praesāgīre, perfect active praesāgīvī or praesāgiī); fourth conjugation, no supine stem

  1. I forebode
    Synonym: praemoneō
